WeSwap

OVERVIEW:
The web platform WeSwap operates as a tool to minimize waste and enhance sustainability in communities. 
Through its item reuse and exchange feature the app develops environmentally friendly practices which lengthens product life cycles as well as deepens community dedication to sustainable purchasing.

OBJECTIVES:
1. Reduce waste
2. Promote sustainable
3. Foster a greener and more connected community


SDGs Targeted: 
Goal 13 Climate action: Through its features the app operates as a climate action solution by lowering industrials pollution levels while reducing demand for products and helping users adopt environment-friendly habits.
Goal 12 Responsible consumption and production: Through its support of item reuse and upcycling the platform promotes responsible consumer practices that diminish waste output.
Goal 11 Sustainable cities and communities: Local meetup spaces and drop-off zones found within the app help develop community-driven sustainability projects to make community more environmentally conscious.

Features:
1. Users of the platform have the ability to share items through posts which feature images and brief descriptions for each item.
2. Customers can locate items through sorting by clothing, electronics and household goods categories.
3. The platform includes chat features for users to schedule exchanges and safe meetings.
4. The dashboard displays both reused items count and estimated waste reduction figures.

